╭─ Assistant [MainThread@1431575] ──────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The patch updates LoopPeel to avoid mutating a shared loop exit condition     │
│ when peeling the last iteration. Specifically, instead of modifying the ICmp  │
│ used by both the header and latch branches, it now:                           │
│                                                                               │
│ - Creates a new compare only for the latch branch to adjust the exit          │
│ condition, preserving the original compare used by the header.                │
│ - If the latch condition is the same Value used by the header branch          │
│ (shared), it conservatively bails out from PeelLast to avoid altering the     │
│ header’s control flow and potentially breaking dominance or equivalence.      │
│                                                                               │
│ Summary of changes in llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/LoopPeel.cpp around lines     │
│ 1174-1183:                                                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ - Replaced in-place mutation of the ICmp with creating a new compare for the  │
│ latch branch using IRBuilder at the latch terminator.                         │
│ - Added a guard to detect if the header branch also uses the same condition   │
│ Value; if so, return false and skip PeelLast rather than trying to adjust     │
│ shared conditions.                                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ This fix addresses the root cause where peeling last iteration was changing   │
│ the header’s branch decision by mutating a compare shared between header and  │
│ latch, leading to incorrect control flow and verifier failures.               │
